        <p id="THE_BISHOP_S_STOREHOUSE">
        THE BISHOP’S STOREHOUSE
        </p>
        <div id="boxdss3" class="clearfix">
            <p id="When_we_were_worn_out_and_released_from_that_calling_we_settle">
            <span id="textspandss13">W</span><span id="textspandss14">hen we were worn out and released from the calling as Housing Coordinators, we settled in and kind of relaxed a little bit and got called to be Assistant Managers to the Bishop’s Storehouse, which is up in Concord. It was in a strip mall area in kind of an old place. The church was building a new building that would house the bishop’s storehouse, the canning facility, and employment facility and social services facility. So we were part of that. <br /><br />As the building was completed, Doug and I were asked to be the team that put together the warehouse, so that was another strenuous physical mission. And we worked and did that for a year. And that was a wonderful, great experience. It was also a very humbling experience, to see the people that needed help and those that came in on a regular basis. We helped fill orders for them, and orders for those being transported far away from this area. <br /><br />I remember a man who came in on a regular basis for quite a while, and he would get eight gallons of milk every time he would come in. And I said, “I don’t mean to pry, but how can you store this milk, or where are you keeping this&#x3f;” He said, “I have five teenage sons, and we go through this amount of milk in a hurry.” And I said, “That is amazing&#x21;” And after about a year of going through this process, he said, “This is the last time I’ll be here&#x3b; I’ve been unemployed, and I finally got a job, and I don’t have to do this anymore.” It was wonderful to witness these people and their resilience. You’re there to help them when there’s a need. It’s nice to see them overcome their need, and move on with their own lives too, so it really was a great experience. We enjoyed it immensely. </span><br />
            </p>
            <div id="blackboxdss2" class="clearfix">
                <p id="by_SKIP_SALMON1">
                by SKIP SALMON
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p id="“We_had_the_first_family_reunion_in_1976_and_I_was_not_able_to">
        <span id="textspandsff2">“Through the years, I witnessed how dedicated, organized and methodically they carried out their daily schedules and served in Church callings. They put all they reasonably could into each calling, blessing many as a result. Upon retiring, Doug and Skip volunteered to serve a full-time mission for the Church. They excelled in not just one mission, but two!  It has been wonderful to see them live healthy, happy, full lives. They are amazing examples and I feel very blessed by them and because of them. Love you, Doug and Skip!”</span><span id="textspandsff3"> </span><span id="textspandsff4"><br /></span><span id="textspandsff5">&#x7e; Judy Salmon, daughter-in-law</span>
        </p>
        <%= image_tag("bishopsstorehouse.png", :id => "bishopsstorehouse", :class => "image") %>
        <%= image_tag("washing dishes.png", :id => "washing_dishes", :class => "image") %>
        <div id="boxdss4" class="clearfix">
            <p id="It_was_nice_to_use_some_of_my_logistics_experience_with_the_fac">
            <span id="textspandss15">I</span><span id="textspandss16">t was nice to use some of my logistics experience with the facility, which made it more comfortable. But there was physical work, lots of physical work. We met a lot of wonderful volunteers who would come up and help. That lasted a year for us. The managers left shortly after that. They had made a change in managers. And we’ve gone back, as volunteers, as often as needed. It was just a wonderful experience to help other people.</span><br />
            </p>
            <div id="blackboxdss3" class="clearfix">
                <p id="by_DOUG_SALMON1">
                by DOUG SALMON
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <span id="“They_didn’t_just_barely_take_care_of_the_things_they_had_to_do">
        <span id="textspandss10">“I’m thankful for Grandma and Grandpa’s testimony of missionary work. They have contributed to my missionary efforts while I served in Peru and I know they have been able to be missionaries in their own area. They are great example of service.”</span><span id="textspandss11"><br /></span><span id="textspandss12">&#x7e; ROBB BIRD, GRANDSON</span>
        </span>
        <div id="linear1" class="clearfix">
        </div>
        <p id="THE_WAY_THEY_SERVED">
        THE BIRTHDAY CAKES</p>
        <div id="True_Servants_Video_Laurie2">
        <iframe src="//player.vimeo.com/video/103572277" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe></div>
        <span id="“Part_of_my_parent’s_legacy_to_me_is_giving_time_to_others_My_">
        <span id="textspandss17">“Part of my parents' legacy to me is giving time to others. My dad, during my teenage years especially, gave me a lot of time of his, which was really precious because he traveled a lot. He took the time to do things with me one-on-one. &#x5b;He showed&#x5d; me how to take time and not be in a hurry and do and enjoy things with others. And he taught me to learn about &#x5b;them&#x5d; and their talents and gifts that they have, and the things they can share with you.”</span><span id="textspandss18"><br /></span><span id="textspandss19">&#x7e; TINA ANDERSEN, DAUGHTER</span>
        </span>
        <p id="MODELS_OF_SERVICE">
        MODELS OF SERVICE
        </p>
        <div id="Examples_of_Service_Tina_Video"><iframe src="//player.vimeo.com/video/103572274" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe></div>
        <span id="“My_mother_is_also_a_great_example_of_giving_her_time_being_">
        <span id="textspandss20">“My mother is also a great example of giving her time,...being there just to listen, and showing love at all costs. I just cannot express how much it means to me to have someone give me her heart and her love and her time, and hopefully I can reiterate that to others.”</span><span id="textspandss21"><br /></span><span id="textspandss22">&#x7e; TINA ANDERSEN, DAUGHTER</span>
        </span>
